{"article_id":"MQJ8rrMceAoYwNVA","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"President Donald Trump and top U.S. health officials addressed the nation Wednesday evening","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"as governments worldwide worked to combat the spread of the new coronavirus .","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"Their comments came","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"as the U.S. saw its first instance of infection in a person","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"without relevant travel history or exposure to another patient","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"known to have the virus .","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"With more than 81,300 cases worldwide and spreading rapidly beyond China to South Korea , Italy and Iran ,","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"the U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention warned Tuesday","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"the virus would spread in the United States","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"and cause `` severe '' disruptions across the country .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"At a news conference the same day in India , President Donald Trump tried to tamp down concerns ,","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"saying","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"the virus was `` very well under control in our country . ''","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"The White House requested $ 2.5 billion in emergency funding this week","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"to combat the outbreak ,","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"but congressional Democrats slammed the request as `` woefully insufficient . ''","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"Coronavirus updates every day :","depth":5},{"id":17,"text":"Get 's Daily Briefing in your inbox","depth":5},{"id":18,"text":"Here 's what the president said Wednesday evening ,","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"and what the facts are .","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"Minutes after Trump downplayed the risk","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"of coronavirus spreading in the United States ,","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"California confirmed a new case","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"that might be the nation ' s first example of a non travel-related case of coronavirus .","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"`` There ' s a chance","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"that it could get worse , \"","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"Trump said .","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"\" There ' s a chance","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"that it could get fairly , substantially worse .","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"But I don ' t think","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"it ' s inevitable ...","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"there ' s a chance","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"that it won ' t spread . ''","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"Less than an hour later , the CDC confirmed the California case","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"involving a person","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"who did not travel to China","depth":13},{"id":36,"text":"and was not known to be exposed to another person there with the virus .","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"The CDC said","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"it ' s unknown how the person was exposed to COVID-19 ,","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"but the agency said","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"it could be the first example of \" community spread , \"","depth":13},{"id":41,"text":"which means an unknown source of infection .","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"The agency has not ruled out","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"that the person was exposed to a traveler with the virus .","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"The first 14 cases","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"confirmed in the United States","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"included 12 travelers","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"returning from China","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"and two individuals","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"who had close contact with those travelers .","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"The California man is the 15th confirmed case ,","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"not counting infected passengers from Diamond Princess and others","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"repatriated from Wuhan , China .","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"On Tuesday , the CDC warned","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"that such community spread of the virus was inevitable","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"and predicted \" severe \" disruptions in everyday life .","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"The agency warned","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"schools could be closed","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"and mass gathering suspended .","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"Coronavirus , explained :","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"Everything","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"to know about Covid-19 , the deadly virus","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"alarming the world","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"Trump compared the small number of COVID-19 cases in the U.S. to the number of flu cases this year","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"and said ,","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"`` The flu in our country kills from 25,000 people to 69,000 people a year .","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"That was shocking to me . ''","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"According to the CDC ,","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"there have been at least 29 million flu illnesses and 16,000 deaths from flu so far this season .","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"The season is not yet over ,","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"but the number of estimated flu deaths so far this year is below the range","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"that Trump cited .","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"The CDC reported","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"annual flu deaths ranged from 12,000 to 61,000 since 2010 , slightly lower than figured","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"the president cited .","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"More :","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"Coronavirus is scary ,","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"but the flu is deadlier , more widespread","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"Trump again compared coronavirus to the flu","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"and predicted","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"a vaccine will soon be available .","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"\" We ' ll essentially have a flu shot for this in a fairly quick manner , \"","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"he said .","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"Anthony Fauci , director of the National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases , also spoke at the news conference","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"and offered a more specific time frame for efforts","depth":14},{"id":85,"text":"to develop a coronavirus vaccine .","depth":14},{"id":86,"text":"He said","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"it will take about two months","depth":15},{"id":88,"text":"to determine","depth":16},{"id":89,"text":"whether a vaccine is safe through a small study in humans .","depth":16},{"id":90,"text":"That would be followed another six to eight months","depth":15},{"id":91,"text":"to conduct a larger , comprehensive medical study","depth":16},{"id":92,"text":"to gauge","depth":17},{"id":93,"text":"whether the vaccine works .","depth":17},{"id":94,"text":"During a Feb. 17 meeting with ' s editorial board meeting , Fauci said","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"it would take at least one year to 18 months","depth":13},{"id":96,"text":"to make a vaccine","depth":14},{"id":97,"text":"that is safe and effective and ready to distribute .","depth":14},{"id":98,"text":"\" The solution to the containment of this current outbreak will not be a vaccine , \"","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"Fauci said .","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"Still , Fauci said","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"the vaccine will be important","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"and would be useful","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"if COVID-19 returns next year as a seasonal respiratory virus .","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"Several drugmakers are working","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"to develop vaccines and other treatments","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"to combat coronavirus .","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"Gilead Sciences , a pharmaceutical company , is testing the antiviral drug remdesivir as a potential coronavirus treatment in several countries .","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"The experimental drug was also used on a suburban Seattle man","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"who became the nation ' s first coronavirus patient .","depth":13},{"id":110,"text":"\" Johns Hopkins ... they did a study , a comprehensive","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"- the countries","depth":15},{"id":112,"text":"best and worst prepared for an epidemic -","depth":15},{"id":113,"text":"and the United States , we ' re rated No . 1 , \"","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"Trump said .","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"Trump was referring to the October 2019 Global Health Security Index by the Johns Hopkins Center for Health Security and the Nuclear Threat Initiative , with research by The Economist Intelligence Unit .","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"The report evaluated the health security capabilities of 195 countries .","depth":13},{"id":117,"text":"While the U.S. ranked No.1 overall ,","depth":14},{"id":118,"text":"the report found","depth":15},{"id":119,"text":"that not a single country in the world is fully prepared to handle an epidemic or pandemic .","depth":15},{"id":120,"text":"The United States scored in the bottom tier of countries for access to health care","depth":15},{"id":121,"text":"\" owing to lack of governmentally guaranteed access to healthcare plus high out-of-pocket expenditures per capita , \"","depth":15},{"id":122,"text":"the report said .","depth":14},{"id":123,"text":"The latest :","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"First coronavirus patient with 'unknown origin ' in the US was n't tested for days","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"Vice President Mike Pence ,","depth":14},{"id":126,"text":"tapped to oversee the Trump administration 's coronavirus response ,","depth":14},{"id":127,"text":"cited his experience","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"handling MERS in Indiana ,","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"where the first U.S. case was confirmed .","depth":13},{"id":130,"text":"In May 2014 , CDC confirmed two cases of MERS , Middle East Respiratory Syndrome , in the United States","depth":14},{"id":131,"text":"- one in Indiana , the other to Florida .","depth":14},{"id":132,"text":"Both cases were health care providers","depth":15},{"id":133,"text":"who lived and worked in Saudi Arabia","depth":16},{"id":134,"text":"and traveled to the United States .","depth":16},{"id":135,"text":"Both were hospitalized in the U.S.","depth":15},{"id":136,"text":"and later discharged","depth":16},{"id":137,"text":"after fully recovering .","depth":16},{"id":138,"text":"MERS ,","depth":14},{"id":139,"text":"which originated in Saudi Arabia ,","depth":14},{"id":140,"text":"resulted in 2,499 cases and 861 deaths worldwide , a fatality rate far higher than SARS or COVID-19 .","depth":13},{"id":141,"text":"More","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"Trump , coronavirus :","depth":10},{"id":143,"text":"Vice President Pence to lead Covid-19 response","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"Trump lauded Pence ' s record on health care","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"when he was governor of Indiana .","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"`` Everybody","depth":17},{"id":147,"text":"who knows anything about health care ,","depth":17},{"id":148,"text":"they look at Indiana , ''","depth":16},{"id":149,"text":"he said .","depth":15},{"id":150,"text":"`` They ' ve established a great health care","depth":16},{"id":151,"text":"( in Indiana ) ...","depth":16},{"id":152,"text":"a lot of other states have looked to .","depth":15},{"id":153,"text":"They wanted to change their health care systems . ''","depth":13},{"id":154,"text":"In 2015 , Indiana implemented sweeping changes to the state ' s Medicaid insurance program ,","depth":14},{"id":155,"text":"requiring low-income adults to pay monthly premiums","depth":15},{"id":156,"text":"to maintain their health insurance coverage .","depth":15},{"id":157,"text":"The reforms were spearheaded by Pence and then-health policy consultant Seema Verma ,","depth":14},{"id":158,"text":"who now oversees the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services .","depth":14},{"id":159,"text":"Republican governors in states","depth":15},{"id":160,"text":"including Kentucky and Arizona ,","depth":15},{"id":161,"text":"also sought federal approval for similar restrictions ,","depth":14},{"id":162,"text":"arguing","depth":14},{"id":163,"text":"such incentives encouraged able-bodied adults to seek employment","depth":15},{"id":164,"text":"and helped curb unnecessary health spending .","depth":15},{"id":165,"text":"But critics said","depth":13},{"id":166,"text":"such restrictions were unnecessarily punitive","depth":14},{"id":167,"text":"and put vulnerable people at risk","depth":15},{"id":168,"text":"of losing their health coverage .","depth":15},{"id":169,"text":"In October ,","depth":12},{"id":170,"text":"facing a federal lawsuit","depth":15},{"id":171,"text":"challenging the state 's work requirement ,","depth":15},{"id":172,"text":"Indiana said","depth":14},{"id":173,"text":"it would postpone eliminating Medicaid benefits for those","depth":14},{"id":174,"text":"who failed to meet the work requirement .","depth":14},{"id":175,"text":"Also during Pence ' s tenure , a small town in Indiana became the center of an HIV epidemic","depth":12},{"id":176,"text":"tied to people","depth":13},{"id":177,"text":"injecting drugs .","depth":13},{"id":178,"text":"In all , 235 people became infected ,","depth":12},{"id":179,"text":"giving Austin , Indiana , an HIV infection rate","depth":13},{"id":180,"text":"rivaling nations in sub-Saharan Africa .","depth":13},{"id":181,"text":"The Pence administration was criticized for its slow response ,","depth":12},{"id":182,"text":"and under pressure allowed a clean-needle exchange","depth":13},{"id":183,"text":"to slow new cases of HIV and hepatitis C infections ,","depth":13},{"id":184,"text":"according to a study","depth":12},{"id":185,"text":"that appeared in The Lancet .","depth":12},{"id":186,"text":"Indiana HIV outbreak :","depth":5},{"id":187,"text":"What to know about Austin 's struggles with drugs and HIV","depth":5},{"id":188,"text":"Trump faced several questions from reporters about the stock market","depth":5},{"id":189,"text":"as U.S. stocks slumped for a fifth straight session on Wednesday .","depth":5},{"id":190,"text":"The President suggested","depth":7},{"id":191,"text":"the Democratic debates played a role in the fall .","depth":7},{"id":192,"text":"\" I think","depth":10},{"id":193,"text":"it took a hit maybe for two reasons .","depth":10},{"id":194,"text":"I think","depth":11},{"id":195,"text":"they take a look at the people","depth":15},{"id":196,"text":"that you watched debating last night","depth":15},{"id":197,"text":"and they say","depth":14},{"id":198,"text":"if there ' s even a possibility","depth":14},{"id":199,"text":"that can happen ,","depth":14},{"id":200,"text":"I think","depth":12},{"id":201,"text":"it really takes a hit","depth":11},{"id":202,"text":"because of that .","depth":11},{"id":203,"text":"And it certainly took a hit","depth":9},{"id":204,"text":"because of this , \"","depth":9},{"id":205,"text":"Trump said ,","depth":8},{"id":206,"text":"referencing the coronavirus outbreak .","depth":8},{"id":207,"text":"Democrats held debates Feb. 19 and Feb. 25 .","depth":5},{"id":208,"text":"On Wednesday , the Dow Jones industrial average slumped 124 points","depth":5},{"id":209,"text":"to close at 26,957.59 ,","depth":5},{"id":210,"text":"after shedding nearly 2,000 points","depth":5},{"id":211,"text":"following steep losses on Monday and Tuesday .","depth":5},{"id":212,"text":"Financial managers have said","depth":4},{"id":213,"text":"investors are reacting to every positive or negative headline about the virus .","depth":4},{"id":214,"text":"Some companies ,","depth":7},{"id":215,"text":"including United Airlines and Mastercard ,","depth":7},{"id":216,"text":"have warned","depth":6},{"id":217,"text":"the outbreak of coronavirus could hurt their finances .","depth":5},{"id":218,"text":"Tech companies","depth":6},{"id":219,"text":"that rely on global sales and supply chains","depth":7},{"id":220,"text":"that could be stifled by the spreading outbreak","depth":7},{"id":221,"text":"were among the 